## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-memory
instruction: Click "Altair Memory" in the main sidebar under "Altair Intelligence."
success_criteria: You are on the Altair Memory page. The stats strip at the top shows total patterns, denial signals, top CARC code, and top denial reason. Three tabs are visible: Patterns, Field Notes, and Industry.
anchor: "Altair Memory"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The link is in the sidebar under "Altair Intelligence."

### step 2
id: read-stats-strip
instruction: Read the stats strip at the top: total patterns, denial signals analyzed, the most frequent CARC code, and the top denial root cause.
success_criteria: You understand the high-level picture of denial activity in your practice.
anchor: "stats strip"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The stats strip is the highlighted bar at the very top of the page.

### step 3
id: browse-patterns
instruction: The Patterns tab is active by default. Each pattern card shows a plain-English summary (e.g., "Payer X denies CPT 36475 without modifier 59"), the CARC code, how many times it's been seen, and whether it's been converted to a scrub rule ("Auto-catching").
success_criteria: You can read denial patterns and understand what recurring issues exist in your practice.
anchor: "pattern cards"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Pattern cards are listed on the page. Each describes a recurring denial issue.

### step 4
id: expand-pattern
instruction: Click on any pattern card to expand it and see a deeper breakdown — including which codes and payers are connected to the issue.
success_criteria: You've expanded a pattern and see additional detail about the codes and payers involved.
anchor: "pattern card"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click on any pattern card to expand it.

## Completion Message
you can now see the denial patterns altair has learned from your claims. patterns that are "auto-catching" already have an active scrub rule. the ones that don't can be converted — go to Scrub Rules to review and activate proposed rules.

